FAm: ye well, shades of famous rhetoricians: fare ye well, worthy teachers, whether it were history, or poetry, or eloquence in the courts that made you famous 3 or whether medicine or Plato’s system won ⁴ you undying renown. And if any care of the living please 'che dead, and if the tribute of 'cheir survivors please them, then take the sad homage of my verse, a fabric of tears and siglis. Undisturbed may your ashes keep their place within the tomb, may the memory of your names live on until that other age return 1 in which, by grace of God our judge, we all shall share!
